page.title: 14Housing,North Radcliffe
page.content: The area has a mixture of different types and ages of houses.The oldest are{terraced}houses dating from the second half of the nineteenth century. They are situated along the main road which runs through the area and on the streets off the main road.There are several new post war estates in the area.These contain{semi-detatched} houses and some{bungalows}There is still new development going on to provide extra housing for people moving into the area.The majority of houses in North Radcliffe are{ {privately}owned.The development of housing has worked its way northwards from the centre of Radcliffe,which is to the south of this area. { { { {}
